                    <birth/>
                    <death>250</death>
                    <floruit>Steward and servant of an Alexandrian magistrate in Roman imperial Egypt.
                      During the persecutions of Decius, Ischyrion’s employer demanded that he renounce Christianity
                      and sacrifice to pagan gods. When Ischyrion refused, the magistrate ordered him beaten and martyred.
                    He is commemorated on 1st of June in the West, 7th of Baʾūnah in the Coptic Church and 7th of Sane in Ethiopia.</floruit>
